                    <span>Calder does a great job in describing the dramatic revolution taking place in the European skies.  For Americans that have witnessed the turmoil that a single efficient operator (Soutwest Airlines) has unleashed on an otherwise inefficient industry, this book is especially interesting.<br>The skies of Europe are deregulated, the gloves are off, and the names are changing.</span>
                  
              
